stylometry:
We are balancing the holding cost of a product with the reordering costs. We could also be balancing a sell out cost if the company decides they will lose money if they run out of inventory. 

You calculate holding costs by taking the number you have left over in inventory and mulitplying it by the cost you incurr having sit in inventory. You calculate reordering costs by taking the amount of product you want to reorder and multiplying that by the cost it is to reorder them. If a sell out cost in incurred you figure out how many units you were off by and multiply that by a cost you decide you have if you sell out.
